28/05/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer said on Thursday (27 May) that Albania, Croatia and Macedonia would receive a positive message at the NATO summit in June. 
The three countries are members of the Adriatic Charter. 
Wrapping up a two-day visit to Tirana, de Hoop Scheffer said his meetings with Albanian authorities helped draw up a joint agenda ahead of the summit. 
He said NATO appreciates the countries' joint efforts on the road to membership, and urged them to continue reforms. 
(Vecernji List - 28/05/04; HINA - 27/05/04)
